          <p class="text-xs text-war-text font-medium mb-2">TRIGGER EVENT</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-war-text-dim">On March 2, 2018, Bleich emailed Kornmeier: "One thing that's been on my mind is how we can make our listing appealing to families. You have us listed as one bed, which probably turns a lot of them off. At minimum, we could include pictures of all bedrooms in the listing, right?" Bleich used the word "bedrooms" (plural) while simultaneously knowing these rooms were illegal. This is direct evidence of intentional fraud — not broker error.</p>
          <p class="font-mono text-xxs text-war-text-muted mt-2">[Dep. Ex. 20; Kornmeier Dep. Tr. 103:9–17]</p>
